Example patch file for testing the nvim-patch-plugin.

This patch demonstrates a simple change to a Lua file.

To test:
1. Run :Code in nvim
2. Paste this patch content (without these comment lines)
3. Press Enter to apply

--- a/test.lua
+++ b/test.lua
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
 local function hello()
-  print("Hello")
+  print("Hello, World!")
+  return true
 end
